127  inline std::string type_string_from_code( DBus::Type t )
128  {
129  switch ( t )
130  {
131  case TYPE_BYTE:
132  return "uint8_t";
133  case TYPE_BOOLEAN:
134  return "bool";
135  case TYPE_INT16:
136  return "int16_t";
137  case TYPE_UINT16:
138  return "uint16_t";
139  case TYPE_INT32:
140  return "int32_t";
141  case TYPE_UINT32:
142  return "uint32_t";
143  case TYPE_INT64:
144  return "int64_t";
145  case TYPE_UINT64:
146  return "uint64_t";
147  case TYPE_DOUBLE:
148  return "double";
149  case TYPE_STRING:
150  return "std::string";
151  case TYPE_OBJECT_PATH:
152  return "DBus::Path";
153  case TYPE_SIGNATURE:
154  return "DBus::Signature";
155  case TYPE_ARRAY:
156  return "std::vector";
157  case TYPE_VARIANT:
158  return "DBus::Variant<>";
159  case TYPE_STRUCT:
160  return "Struct";
161  case TYPE_DICT_ENTRY:
162  return "std::pair<>";
163  case TYPE_UNIX_FD:
164  return "FileDescriptor";
165  default:
166  break;
167  }
168  return std::string("Invalid");
169  }
